---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import TimeLineElement from "../components/cv/TimeLine.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Resume" sideBarActiveItemID="cv">
  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Profile</div>
  </div>

  <div class="mb-10 text-justify">
    Web Application Developer with 9+ years of experience in full-stack web
    development. Expertise in PHP, Python, JavaScript, and React with a proven
    track record of designing, developing, and maintaining scalable web
    applications. Strong proficiency in debugging, code review, and
    troubleshooting. Continuous learner with hands-on experience in modern
    frameworks (Laravel, FastAPI, React) and cloud technologies (AWS, Docker).
    Skilled at optimizing application performance and collaborating with
    development teams across Windows and Linux environments. Bilingual: English
    and Spanish (native speaker).
  </div>

  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Education</div>
  </div>

  <div class="time-line-container grid gap-4 mb-10">
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Bachelor of Science in Computer Engineering"
      subtitle="2016 at Universidad Nihon Gakko, Asunción, Paraguay"
    />
  </div>

  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Experience</div>
  </div>

  <div class="time-line-container mb-10">
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Senior Web Application Developer"
      subtitle="From July 2020 to Present at Main Library, University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign, Champaign, IL"
    >
      Developed and maintained scalable web applications using PHP, SQL, and
      JavaScript, ensuring high performance and usability through rigorous
      testing and optimization. Managed the full deployment lifecycle by
      orchestrating Docker-based virtual environments and AWS cloud
      infrastructure. Streamlined development workflows by implementing CI/CD
      pipelines and version control with Git, while providing rapid technical
      troubleshooting and cross-functional support.
    </TimeLineElement>
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Web Application Developer"
      subtitle="From August 2014 to August 2019 at Opción Creativa, Asunción, Paraguay"
    >
      Acted as a technical representative in executive meetings to align
      development milestones with strategic goals. Leveraged PHP, SQL, and
      JavaScript to design and monitor high-performance websites within UNIX and
      Apache environments. Managed the entire QA lifecycle, from initial
      deployment to end-to-end issue resolution, ensuring all deployments met
      rigorous performance and scalability standards.
    </TimeLineElement>
    <TimeLineElement
      title="IT Support Specialist"
      subtitle="From August 2015 to August 2019 at Weldon SA, Asunción, Paraguay"
    >
      Collaborated with development teams to identify software defects and
      implement critical version fixes, ensuring system stability. Managed
      end-user technical support by resolving complex issues while proactively
      protecting infrastructure by removing malware and patching
      vulnerabilities. Monitored the operational status of web and email servers
      and configured workstations to maintain smooth business continuity and
      data protection.
    </TimeLineElement>
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Lecturer"
      subtitle="From February 2018 to August 2019 at Universidad Nihon Gakko, Asunción, Paraguay"
    >
      Delivered lectures and practical demonstrations for three undergraduate
      courses, translating complex technical concepts into accessible learning
      outcomes. Integrated modern instructional technologies and online
      platforms to enhance student engagement and modernize the computer science
      curriculum.
    </TimeLineElement>
  </div>

  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Projects & Continuous Learning</div>
  </div>

  <div class="time-line-container mb-10">
    <TimeLineElement title="PHP Laravel Projects">
      Development of REST APIs and web applications using the Laravel framework
      with emphasis on database design, authentication mechanisms, and
      middleware implementation.
    </TimeLineElement>
    <TimeLineElement title="Python FastAPI Projects">
      Building high-performance asynchronous web services and APIs using FastAPI
      with robust data validation, dependency injection patterns, and automated
      API documentation.
    </TimeLineElement>
    <TimeLineElement title="React Frontend Applications">
      Creation of responsive and interactive user interfaces using React with
      advanced state management, modern React hooks, and component-based
      architecture best practices.
    </TimeLineElement>
    <TimeLineElement title="WordPress Custom Themes & WooCommerce">
      Design and development of custom WordPress themes integrated with
      WooCommerce for e-commerce functionality including payment processing and
      inventory management systems.
    </TimeLineElement>
  </div>

  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Certifications</div>
  </div>

  <ul class="list-disc mx-6 mb-10 grid gap-2">
    <li>
      <a
        href="https://credentials.edx.org/credentials/9c006cec2c524390aa41684abf81cf7e/"
        target="_blank"
      >
        Micromasters in Cloud Computing - University of Maryland, Edx. 2023</a
      >
    </li>
    <li>
      <a
        href="https://credentials.edx.org/credentials/f036f44d8f324e5fb4ac0aa3fb4dbc88/"
        target="_blank"
        >I.T. Project Management - University of Washington, Edx. 2022</a
      >
    </li>
  </ul>

  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Skills</div>
  </div>

  <ul class="list-disc md:columns-5 columns-2 mx-6">
    <li>Spanish (Native)</li>
    <li>English (Fluent)</li>
    <li>PHP</li>
    <li>Python</li>
    <li>Node.js</li>
    <li>Laravel</li>
    <li>FastAPI</li>
    <li>React</li>
    <li>HTML</li>
    <li>CSS</li>
    <li>Responsive Design</li>
    <li>Tailwind CSS</li>
    <li>Bootstrap</li>
    <li>PostgreSQL</li>
    <li>MySQL</li>
    <li>Git/GitHub</li>
    <li>Docker</li>
    <li>AWS</li>
    <li>CI/CD</li>
    <li>Apache/Nginx</li>
    <li>Linux</li>
    <li>WordPress</li>
    <li>WooCommerce</li>
    <li>REST API Design</li>
    <li>Debugging</li>
    <li>Code Review</li>
  </ul>
</BaseLayout>
